  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - By reason of insufficient evidence provided, the applicant has failed to demonstrate that the unit has been vacant for a continuous period of at least 3 months immediately prior to the date of the application for prior approval. The proposal would therefore fail to comply with condition MA.1(a) of Part 3 of Schedule 2 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 (as amended).\r\n\r\nIn addition to this, the subject property is located within the Putney Town Centre site where an Article 4 Direction is in place that removes permitted development rights for the change of use from commercial, business and service uses (Use Class E) to residential uses (Use Class C3). This means that a change of use from commercial, business and service uses (Use Class E) to residential uses (Use Class C3) is prohibited without planning permission in this instance.\r\n"
